ction; and the accretion rate $\\dot M \\ll \\dot M_B$. The\npredominantly radial magnetic field created by the MTI at large radii in\nspherical accretion flows may account for the stable Faraday rotation measure\ntowards Sgr A* in the Galactic Center.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Apr 2008 20:14:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 5 Jul 2008 22:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
